Package ohos.utils

Class LightweightSet<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.utils.LightweightSet<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, Set<E>

    public final class LightweightSet<E>
extends Object
implements Collection<E>, Set<E>
    Provides a container that implements the Collection and Set interfaces.

    The LightweightSet container uses less memory than the HashSet container, but may show poor performance when reaching a large size.

    It is recommended that you use this container when less memory is required.

    Note: The thread is secure only when data is read from the LightweightSet container.

    Since:
    1

      • removeAt

        public E removeAt​(int index)
        Deletes an object at the location identified by index from an LightweightSet container.

        If index is a negative number, the object is located from the reverse direction.

        During the deletion, the system determines whether to expand or reduce capacity of the LightweightSet container. If the number of objects in the container is less than a specified number, the system reduces the capacity of the container.

        Parameters:
        index - Identifies the location of an object.
        Returns:
        Returns the object identified by index.

      • valueAt

        public E valueAt​(int index,
                 E defaultKey)
        Obtains the object at the location identified by index in an LightweightSet container.

        If index is a negative number, the object is located from the reverse direction.

        If the index is invalid (for example, it is greater than the number of objects in the LightweightSet container or less than 0), defaultKey will be returned.

        Parameters:
        index - Identifies the location of an object.
        defaultKey - Indicates the default value returned if the specified index is invalid.
        Returns:
        Returns the object identified by index in the LightweightSet container.
